<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="626" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-15"><hi rend="italic">November 15,
                                    1895</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Demand payment for burned buildings. What cooperation in what measures is
                            referred to?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
